<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Public Finance Associate</h1>

<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>
<p class="bac">Banc of America Securities Public Finance is one of the top municipal underwriters nationally.  Organized by region and specialty, our Investment Bankers are dedicated to understanding the unique operating environments of our clients, and to building strong, enduring client relationships. We are organized into 6 regional and 8 specialty teams.  Regional teams cover state and local governments across the United States; specialty teams cover tax exempt financing for economic development, energy, healthcare, higher education, housing, not-for-profit organizations, student loans, tax-exempt corporate, transportation and water and sewer.  </p>
<p class="bac">As a leader in tax exempt financing, our Public Finance team delivers creative solutions for issuers and investors across a range of municipal debt offerings and associated products including:  municipal bonds, taxable, fixed, floating, and auction rate securities, short term financing, reinvestment of bond proceeds and interest rate risk management. The Banc of America Securities Public Finance Group is a fully integrated team of specialists dedicated to helping clients to structure and issue tax exempt debt.</p>
<p class="bac">What&acute;s our strategy for success? It starts and ends with serving our clients the solutions and execution they need in today&acute;s market.  Our investment bankers work closely with commercial bankers, sales, trading and underwriting to develop strategic solutions for our clients, leveraging the full power of Bank of America&acute;s franchise.</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">As an active team member focused on a region or specialty area, associates help orchestrate capital raising and strategic advisory transactions.  Associates are called on to:  </p>

<ul class="bac">
	<li>Develop and manage financial models • Create various financial analyses, based on product and market dynamics</li>
	<li>Perform comprehensive and in-depth company and industry research</li>
	<li>Prepare presentation and other materials for clients</li>
	<li>Participate in due diligence sessions and client meetings</li>
	<li>Interact with deal team members and clients</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>
<p class="bac">Candidates must demonstrate a combination of academic aptitude, quantitative skills, computer skills, strategic and creative thinking and distinguished written and oral communications skills. Associates are required to manage several projects at once and work effectively as an individual and as part of a team. Some common driving characteristics we look for:  assertiveness, attention to detail, exceptional academic achievement, initiative, team focus, leadership, self-confidence, strategic and creative thinking capabilities, strong work ethic, and strong communication skills. </p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training</h2>
<p class="bac">As a Public Finance Associate you will begin your career at Bank of America with an intensive training program. Initially, you will train with your peers from other lines of business. You will then participate in a program designed specifically for Global Markets Associates.   The program is an interactive, experientially based mix of  group projects, elearning, lectures, case studies, business representative presentations and teambuilding activities which will provide you with a solid grounding in global markets and economics and how Bank of America's businesses, products and services operate in this global context.   Throughout the program you will have ample opportunity to meet and work with your peers and other colleagues across all levels of the Bank. The network you build during this time will be a tremendous resource to you throughout your career.</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Full-Time Placement</h2>
<p class="bac">Positions may be in New York or Charlotte.  Offers are made for a specific office and specific industry or product group, based on candidate preference and business need. Throughout the recruiting and orientation process candidates have the opportunity to learn about each group and meet team members.</p>


<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

